entries.femaleVariant: [Open]
Empty… Heh. Damn.
Hello, V. Man, time flies.
Inferred death just ain't what it used to be…
Key word – inferred. But Abernathy is purging the dep. Purged me. They took my house, accounts, implants…
But I'm not done. Gonna prove she was wrong about me, shove it down her throat.
Ah, so you make your move steppin' on me. Gonna serve my head up on a silver platter – and you think Abernathy'll welcome you back, arms outstretched?
entries.maleVariant: Ah, so you make your move steppin' on me. Gonna serve my head up on a silver platter? And you think Abernathy'll welcome you back, arms outstretched?

entries.femaleVariant: I'm nobody to Abernathy.
Listen, Frank. I'm nobody to Abernathy. Prolly doesn't know I exist, if she ever knew.
You had it in for her, V, were setting her up. People don't forget shit like that.
You're pathetic.
'Member Joey Livani? Gonk from mergers and acquisitions? Pissed himself the day he was fired.
What the fuck are you talking about?
No, wa'n't me. That was Jenkins' thing. Used me as his tool.
entries.maleVariant: No, that wasn't me. That was Jenkins' thing. Just used me as his tool.

entries.femaleVariant: Always were arrogant. No, no time to chat, too busy with something super important.
Whoa, about to piss yourself, too. Can smell it comin'.
Fuck you sideways, V. You and this whole rotten city.
You really don't care if I end you.
Gotta start over.
Not my problem.
Dunno. And frankly, don't give the slimmest shit.
Thanks for your honesty, V. Good to know exactly where I stand.
You're right. Going back to Arasaka... it's suicide, one way or another.
Huh. Miss the warmth of the corporate lap? That unique thrill of internal power struggles?
Butt out.
Butt out, not your biz.
Hm, I get it, fine. I'm gonna go take a piss.
Got a few scores to settle.
What? Got a score to settle is all.
A-hah. I knew it, I knew it, I knew it. Rat's still in the race.
Don'tcha need to be somewhere else? Your piece need oilin', guitar need tunin' maybe?
entries.maleVariant: Don'tcha need to be somewhere else? Your piece need oiling, guitar needs tunin' maybe?

entries.femaleVariant: That's about the size of it. Now turn, hands on your head, hop to it.
Here's another idea - I kill you right here and now.
Shoulda checked my schedule. Got plans for this evening.
entries.maleVariant: Shoulda checked my schedule. Got plans for this evenin'.

entries.femaleVariant: Mhm. Namely?
'Bout to find out.
Saw him as the most pathetic guy ever at Arasaka. Not so anymore. You just took that title.
His knees were shakin' so much he couldn't even walk. Guards had to drag 'im out to the curb.
Go ahead, try.
Want you to open your eyes.
Go ahead an' try, Frank. C'mon. Lemme see what you're capable of.
Open your eyes, Frank. Arasaka threw you out like so much trash... and you're gonna go back and beg for mercy, knowing they have none to give?
Lots of people have gone back.
Lots – nah, some – sure. To a good brain cleansing, just in case. That what you really want?
It's a closed book, Frank. Gotta refigure your life. Game over, start again.
Start again… Got nothing to start with, less!
Got iron and a full clip. Add a little gumption – you're good to go in NC.
Keep it together, Frank.
So, what? Back to the office? Recently fired employee walks in, gun in hand. They'll shoot you, then put me down.
entries.maleVariant: So, what? Back to the office? Recently fired employee walks in, gun in hand? They'll shoot you, and then put me down.

entries.femaleVariant: Maybe. But see, V, the problem is I have nothing to lose.
Clearly won't change your mind, but... not about to die with you, either.
entries.maleVariant: Clearly won't change your mind. But I'm not about to die with you, either.

entries.femaleVariant: So what'm I supposed to do? Huh? What the fuck can I do?
Sometimes the simplest solutions get it done.
Heh. Fuuuck…
Nothin' like runnin' into old friends and reminiscin', huh? Ah, the golden olden days…
Not in the mood, Johnny.
Should be. Look at your luck. I mean, coulda wound up all jittery like him.
Have a nice night, V. I'll be at home.
You're not goin' anywhere!
